title: Truck, car and motorcycle show in Kenton Saturday, Oct. 10
text: Truck, car and motorcycle show in Kenton Saturday, Oct. 10 The Kenton Ruritan Club's annual truck, car and motorcycle show, originally planned for last Saturday, has been rescheduled to this Saturday, Oct. 10. Proceeds benefit Kay's Kamp for children with cancer. Comment By Staff Report Posted Oct. 9, 2015 @ 10:32 am The Kenton Ruritan Club's annual truck, car and motorcycle show will be held this Saturday, Oct. 10 at the former Kenton School on Main Street (Route 300) from 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. The show was originally planned for last Saturday but was postponed because of rain. Registration this Saturday will be from 9 a.m. to noon. Awards will be at 2 p.m. The fee is $10. Dash plaques will be presented to the first 75 vehicles to register. Three trophies will be awarded in each category, plus a "best in show" trophy. Music will be provided by Elite D.J. Services. There will be food for sale and 50/50 raffle and more. Vendor spaces are available for $15. Proceeds from the show benefit Kay's Kamp for children fighting cancer. For more information, call Marc Gray, (302) 670-9112, or Eddie McMullen, (302) 668-8432.
